The paper deals with submodular function maximization, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are both relevant sub-categories as they deal with the theoretical aspects of algorithm design and analysis. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also relevant as submodular functions have applications in information theory. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as submodular functions are used in optimization problems in machine learning. Finally, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the difficulty of derandomizing algorithms for submodular function maximization.
